Hochtief Executives May Quit on ACS Takeover, Manager Reports

-- B y   R i c h a r d   W e i s s
-- 
2011-03-31T10:25:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-31/hochtief-executives-may-quit-on-acs-takeover-manager-reports.html
Three members of  Hochtief AG (HOT) ’s
management board may resign because the company is being taken
over by  Spain ’s Actividades de Construccion & Servicios SA,
 Manager Magazin  reported, citing unidentified people with inside
knowledge of the matter.  Chief Financial Officer Burkhard Lohr may leave the
company, according to the magazine’s April edition. Two other
executives, Martin Rohr and Frank Stieler, may also resign. The
total value of severance packages for board members quitting
upon change of control at the company could top 60 million euros
($85 million), the magazine said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Weiss in  Frankfurt  at 
 rweiss5@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at   bkammel@bloomberg.net . 